here is a programming construct in javascript that calculates the factorial of a number. the function is written to take a non-negative integer as input and returns its factorial. for demonstration purposes, we will use the value 7.

```javascript
function factorial(x) {
  let result = 1;
  for (let i = 1; i <= x; i++) {
    result *= i;
  }
  return result;
}

let x = 7;
let result = factorial(x);
console.log("the factorial of " + x + " is " + result);
```

